{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"semimythic-bubonic-camel","description":"## Context\nA3 (34b1) auto-remediation drove SNAPSHOT_INCONSISTENT to zero on the shared store but, by design, LEFT the order-sensitive human-triage faults for manual reconciliation. `rebar fsck` currently reports 13 ORPHAN_EVENT + 1 MISSING_CREATE.\n\n## Why auto-repair is unsafe here (verified)\nAll 13 orphans are pre-snapshot **EDIT** events (assignee edits) absent from the snapshot's `source_event_uuids`. Running the deterministic full-log rebuild (`rebar fsck --repair-snapshots`) on them was tested and CORRUPTED state — 11 of 13 tickets flipped `closed → in_progress` because the rebuild reorders STATUS events. That change was reverted before any push. So each orphan needs a per-ticket human decision, not a blanket rebuild.\n\n## Affected tickets\n- ORPHAN_EVENT (EDIT): 183e, 7522, 7e48, 95dc, ba2c, baf7, c156, cc5b, d6cc, e6f9, e8eb, f112, fa98\n- MISSING_CREATE: 9fa4-e87a-a5f0-4b7c\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] For each of the 13 EDIT orphans: decide whether the orphan edit should be folded (and if so, reconcile the resulting status so the ticket stays `closed`) or retired as stale — record the decision per ticket.\n- [ ] For 9fa4 MISSING_CREATE: determine the correct disposition (reconstruct a CREATE, archive, or accept) and apply it.\n- [ ] `rebar fsck` reports zero ORPHAN_EVENT + zero MISSING_CREATE, with no ticket's displayed status/assignee changed incorrectly.\n- [ ] Decisions recorded as a comment on this ticket.","id":"115b-ceea-09f8-4a93","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Human-triage the 14 residual fsck orphans (13 EDIT ORPHAN_EVENT + 1 MISSING_CREATE)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783552665432545001,"uuid":"22526f38-dcda-4f11-8152-b839e6360653"}